race.comment: Competitive. PRINZERRO (1) is third up and can show here best back in grade. Just felt the pinch first-up before being slightly disappointing last time out at Seymour. This shapes as a much better race for him as he hits this ready to peak and a much better effort is on the cards. BAKERSBEND (10) was an easy Maiden winner at Swan Hill and then went back and was on the pace again and didn't finish it off. Has a strong record at this distance, and fourth up can get back on track. JAMMIN JIMMY (7) comes here third-up and poised to strike from an inside barrier. He wasn't disgraced at Swan Hill last time out and with further improvement expected, he can feature. HE'S GODSPEED (6) is better than he showed last time out and can bounce back.
